15/01/2010
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The government has no plans to amend the controversial smoking ban that took effect on January 1st, Deputy Prime Minister for Economic Affairs Vladimir Pesevski said on Thursday (January 14th).
He explained that similar laws are effective in other countries and long-term economic effects are positive.
Smoking is now banned in all restaurants and bars in Macedonia.
Stiff fines are given to violators and establishment owners.
Business owners have threatened to close their bars and restaurants on January 22nd in protest.
(A1, Makfax, Sitel, Alsat, MIA - 14/01/10)
